lpEnetCidDataTable.name: lpEnetCidDataTable
lpEnetCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

lpEnetCustomerIdentifier.name: lpEnetCustomerIdentifier
lpEnetCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

lpEnetIfEntryTable.name: lpEnetIfEntryTable
lpEnetIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

lpEnetIfAdminStatus.name: lpEnetIfAdminStatus
lpEnetIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpEnetIfIndex.name: lpEnetIfIndex
lpEnetIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

lpEnetProvTable.name: lpEnetProvTable
lpEnetProvTable.description: This group contains provisioned attributes for the Ethernet component.

lpEnetHeartbeatPacket.name: lpEnetHeartbeatPacket
lpEnetHeartbeatPacket.description: The heartbeat packet feature is used to select whether or not the station will generate a heartbeat packet. If enabled, the station will generate one heartbeat packet every second. If disabled, the station will not generate any heartbeat packets.

lpEnetApplicationFramerName.name: lpEnetApplicationFramerName
lpEnetApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Ethernet component. This link is used by the component administration system (CAS) to identify which card the application component (associated with the Framer component) is to be created.

lpEnetAdminInfoTable.name: lpEnetAdminInfoTable
lpEnetAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

lpEnetVendor.name: lpEnetVendor
lpEnetVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

lpEnetCommentText.name: lpEnetCommentText
lpEnetCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

lpEnetStateTable.name: lpEnetStateTable
lpEnetStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

lpEnetAdminState.name: lpEnetAdminState
lpEnetAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

lpEnetOperationalState.name: lpEnetOperationalState
lpEnetOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

lpEnetUsageState.name: lpEnetUsageState
lpEnetUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

lpEnetOperStatusTable.name: lpEnetOperStatusTable
lpEnetOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

lpEnetSnmpOperStatus.name: lpEnetSnmpOperStatus
lpEnetSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpEnetOperTable.name: lpEnetOperTable
lpEnetOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Ethernet component.

lpEnetMacAddress.name: lpEnetMacAddress
lpEnetMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is only recognized by one station on the network The value of this attribute will be assigned by the system. MAC address is displayed in canonical format.

lpEnetStatsTable.name: lpEnetStatsTable
lpEnetStatsTable.description: This group contains statistical attributes for the Ethernet component.

lpEnetAlignmentErrors.name: lpEnetAlignmentErrors
lpEnetAlignmentErrors.description: The alignmentErrors counter indicates the number of frames received which were not an integral number of octets in length. Frames will be checked for alignmentErrors before they are checked for Frame Check Sequence (FCS) errors. If there is an alignment error, the error will only be counted here and not in fcsErrors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetFcsErrors.name: lpEnetFcsErrors
lpEnetFcsErrors.description: The fcsErrors, Frame Check Sequence (FCS) error, counter indicates the number of frames received which were an integral number of octets in length and did not pass the FCS check. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetSingleCollisionFrames.name: lpEnetSingleCollisionFrames
lpEnetSingleCollisionFrames.description: The singleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced exactly one collision. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames.name: lpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames
lpEnetMultipleCollisionFrames.description: The multipleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced more than one collision. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetSqeTestErrors.name: lpEnetSqeTestErrors
lpEnetSqeTestErrors.description: The sqeTestErrors, Signal Quality Error (SQE) Test errors, counter indicates the number of times the 'SQE Test Error' message has been generated for the station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetDeferredTransmissions.name: lpEnetDeferredTransmissions
lpEnetDeferredTransmissions.description: The deferredTransmissions counter indicates the number of frames which experienced a transmission delay because the medium was busy. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetLateCollisions.name: lpEnetLateCollisions
lpEnetLateCollisions.description: The lateCollisions counter indicates the number of times a collision was detected later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetExcessiveCollisions.name: lpEnetExcessiveCollisions
lpEnetExcessiveCollisions.description: The excessiveCollisions counter indicates the number of frames which failed to get transmitted due to excessive collisions. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetMacTransmitErrors.name: lpEnetMacTransmitErrors
lpEnetMacTransmitErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) transmit error counter indicates the number of times that a transmission failed due to internal MAC transmit errors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetCarrierSenseErrors.name: lpEnetCarrierSenseErrors
lpEnetCarrierSenseErrors.description: The carrier sense error counter indicates the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetFrameTooLongs.name: lpEnetFrameTooLongs
lpEnetFrameTooLongs.description: The frame too long counter indicates the number of frames received which exceeded the maximum frame size. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetMacReceiveErrors.name: lpEnetMacReceiveErrors
lpEnetMacReceiveErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) receive error counter indicates the number of times a receive failed due to internal MAC receive errors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEnetTestType.name: lpEnetTestType
lpEnetTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

lpEnetTestFrmSize.name: lpEnetTestFrmSize
lpEnetTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

lpEnetTestDuration.name: lpEnetTestDuration
lpEnetTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

lpEnetTestResultsTable.name: lpEnetTestResultsTable
lpEnetTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

lpEnetTestElapsedTime.name: lpEnetTestElapsedTime
lpEnetTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

lpEnetTestTimeRemaining.name: lpEnetTestTimeRemaining
lpEnetTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

lpEnetTestCauseOfTermination.name: lpEnetTestCauseOfTermination
lpEnetTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

lpEnetTestFrmTx.name: lpEnetTestFrmTx
lpEnetTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpEnetTestBitsTx.name: lpEnetTestBitsTx
lpEnetTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpEnetTestFrmRx.name: lpEnetTestFrmRx
lpEnetTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpEnetTestBitsRx.name: lpEnetTestBitsRx
lpEnetTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpEnetTestErroredFrmRx.name: lpEnetTestErroredFrmRx
lpEnetTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpFiCidDataTable.name: lpFiCidDataTable
lpFiCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

lpFiCustomerIdentifier.name: lpFiCustomerIdentifier
lpFiCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

lpFiIfEntryTable.name: lpFiIfEntryTable
lpFiIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

lpFiIfAdminStatus.name: lpFiIfAdminStatus
lpFiIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpFiIfIndex.name: lpFiIfIndex
lpFiIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

lpFiSmtProvTable.name: lpFiSmtProvTable
lpFiSmtProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable Station Management (SMT) attributes of the Fddi component.

lpFiUserData.name: lpFiUserData
lpFiUserData.description: The user data field is used to identify the FDDI interface on the ring. The user data contains a message with a maximum of 32 characters.

lpFiAcceptAa.name: lpFiAcceptAa
lpFiAcceptAa.description: The acceptAa attribute defines the station type A to station type A connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiAcceptBb.name: lpFiAcceptBb
lpFiAcceptBb.description: The acceptBb attribute defines the station type B to station type B connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiAcceptAs.name: lpFiAcceptAs
lpFiAcceptAs.description: The acceptAs attribute defines the station type A to station type S connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiAcceptBs.name: lpFiAcceptBs
lpFiAcceptBs.description: The acceptBs attribute defines the station type B to station type S connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiAcceptAm.name: lpFiAcceptAm
lpFiAcceptAm.description: The acceptAm attribute defines the station type A to station type M connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiAcceptBm.name: lpFiAcceptBm
lpFiAcceptBm.description: The acceptBm attribute defines the station type B to station type M connection policy. If enabled, the connection will be accepted. If disabled, the connection will be rejected.

lpFiUseThruBa.name: lpFiUseThruBa
lpFiUseThruBa.description: The useThruBa attribute is used to configure the requested path of the associated station. If enabled, only the secondary preferred path is permitted. If disabled, only the primary preferred path is permitted.

lpFiNeighborNotifyInterval.name: lpFiNeighborNotifyInterval
lpFiNeighborNotifyInterval.description: The neighborNotifyInterval attribute contains the amount of time, expressed in seconds, between neighbor notification frames.

lpFiStatusReportPolicy.name: lpFiStatusReportPolicy
lpFiStatusReportPolicy.description: The statusReportPolicy attribute indicates whether or not the station will generate status reporting frames for its implemented events and conditions. If true, the station will generate the status frames. If false, the station will not generate the status frames.

lpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer.name: lpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer
lpFiTraceMaxExpirationTimer.description: The traceMaxExpirationTimer attribute is used to configure the maximum propagation time, expressed in milliseconds, for a trace on a FDDI topology. This value places a lower bound on the detection time for an unrecovered ring.

lpFiApplicationFramerName.name: lpFiApplicationFramerName
lpFiApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Fddi component. This defines which LanApplication/n Framer will be using this Fddi interface.

lpFiMacProvTable.name: lpFiMacProvTable
lpFiMacProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable MAC attributes of the Fddi component.

lpFiTokenRequestTimer.name: lpFiTokenRequestTimer
lpFiTokenRequestTimer.description: The tokenRequestTimer value contains the token request value assigned to the associated medium access controller (MAC). Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

lpFiTokenMaxTimer.name: lpFiTokenMaxTimer
lpFiTokenMaxTimer.description: The tokenMaxTimer value is the maximum timer value the negotiated token rotation time may assume. Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

lpFiValidTransmissionTimer.name: lpFiValidTransmissionTimer
lpFiValidTransmissionTimer.description: The validTransmissionTimer (Tvx) value specifies the amount of time required for a valid transmission. The station must receive a valid transmission once every Tvx. Warning: Changes to this attribute can have adverse effects on the performance of the FDDI ring. Therefore it is recommended that this parameter only be modified by personnel with a thorough understanding of the consequences that may result from changes to this attribute.

lpFiAdminInfoTable.name: lpFiAdminInfoTable
lpFiAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

lpFiVendor.name: lpFiVendor
lpFiVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

lpFiCommentText.name: lpFiCommentText
lpFiCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

lpFiStateTable.name: lpFiStateTable
lpFiStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

lpFiAdminState.name: lpFiAdminState
lpFiAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

lpFiOperationalState.name: lpFiOperationalState
lpFiOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

lpFiUsageState.name: lpFiUsageState
lpFiUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

lpFiOperStatusTable.name: lpFiOperStatusTable
lpFiOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

lpFiSnmpOperStatus.name: lpFiSnmpOperStatus
lpFiSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpFiSmtOperTable.name: lpFiSmtOperTable
lpFiSmtOperTable.description: This group contains the operational station management (SMT) attributes of the Fddi component.

lpFiVersion.name: lpFiVersion
lpFiVersion.description: The version attribute contains a copy of the currently supported version numbers of the management information base (MIB) and the station management (SMT).

lpFiBypassPresent.name: lpFiBypassPresent
lpFiBypassPresent.description: The bypassPresent attribute indicates whether the optical bypass switch is present on its AB port pair. If true, the optical bypass switch is present. If false, it is not present.

lpFiEcmState.name: lpFiEcmState
lpFiEcmState.description: The ecmState, Entity Coordination Manager (ECM), state indicates the current state of the ECM state machine.

lpFiCfState.name: lpFiCfState
lpFiCfState.description: The cfState attribute indicates the current state of the configuration management (CFM) state machine.

lpFiMacOperTable.name: lpFiMacOperTable
lpFiMacOperTable.description: This group contains the operational Medium Access Controller (MAC) attributes of the of the Fddi component.

lpFiRingLatency.name: lpFiRingLatency
lpFiRingLatency.description: The ringLatency attribute contains the measured ring latency of the ring the station is attached to.

lpFiMacAddress.name: lpFiMacAddress
lpFiMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is recognized by only one station on the attached ring. The value of this attribute is assigned by the system. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncMacAddress.

lpFiUpstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiUpstreamNeighbor
lpFiUpstreamNeighbor.description: The upstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the upstream neighbor station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncUpstreamNeighbor.

lpFiDownstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiDownstreamNeighbor
lpFiDownstreamNeighbor.description: The downstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncDownstreamNeighbor.

lpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor
lpFiOldUpstreamNeighbor.description: The oldUpstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the upstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncOldUpstreamNeighbor.

lpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor
lpFiOldDownstreamNeighbor.description: The oldDownstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in canonical format. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncOldDownstreamNeighbor.

lpFiDupAddressTest.name: lpFiDupAddressTest
lpFiDupAddressTest.description: The dupAddressTest attribute indicates the condition results of the duplicate address test. If notDone, the test has not been executed. If pass, the test has successfully executed. If fail, the test has failed.

lpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer.name: lpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer
lpFiTokenNegotiatedTimer.description: The tokenNegotiatedTimer specifies the negotiated token rotation time.

lpFiFrameCounts.name: lpFiFrameCounts
lpFiFrameCounts.description: The frameCounts attribute contains the number of frames that have been received by the station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiCopiedCounts.name: lpFiCopiedCounts
lpFiCopiedCounts.description: The copiedCounts attribute contains the number of frames successfully copied into this station's receive buffers, not including MAC control frames. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiTransmitCounts.name: lpFiTransmitCounts
lpFiTransmitCounts.description: The transmitCounts attribute contains the number of frames transmitted by this station, not including MAC control frames. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiErrorCounts.name: lpFiErrorCounts
lpFiErrorCounts.description: The errorCounts attribute contains the number of error frames first detected by this station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiLostCounts.name: lpFiLostCounts
lpFiLostCounts.description: The lostCounts attribute contains the number of instances that the station has detected a format error during frame reception such that the frame was stripped. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiRmtState.name: lpFiRmtState
lpFiRmtState.description: The rmtState, ring management (RMT), state indicates the current state of the RMT state machine.

lpFiFrameErrorFlag.name: lpFiFrameErrorFlag
lpFiFrameErrorFlag.description: The frameErrorFlag attribute indicates the MAC frame error condition status. If true, a MAC frame error is present. If false, a MAC frame error condition is not present.

lpFiMacCOperTable.name: lpFiMacCOperTable
lpFiMacCOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Medium Access Controller (MAC) Counters Table of the Fddi component.

lpFiTokenCounts.name: lpFiTokenCounts
lpFiTokenCounts.description: The tokenCounts attribute contains the number of times the station has received a token. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiTvxExpiredCounts.name: lpFiTvxExpiredCounts
lpFiTvxExpiredCounts.description: The tvxExpiredCounts, Transmission Valid eXpired (TVX), attribute contains the number of times that TVX timer has expired. This counter may increment as stations go on and off the ring. A rapidly increasing value may indicate a problem. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiNotCopiedCounts.name: lpFiNotCopiedCounts
lpFiNotCopiedCounts.description: The notCopiedCounts attribute contains the number of times that the station has detected a frame addressed to itself but did not copy it due to local buffer congestion. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiLateCounts.name: lpFiLateCounts
lpFiLateCounts.description: The lateCounts attribute contains the number of token rotation time (TRT) expirations since the station was reset or a token was received. This counter may increment as stations go on and off the ring. A rapidly increasing value may indicate a problem. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiRingOpCounts.name: lpFiRingOpCounts
lpFiRingOpCounts.description: The ringOpCounts attribute contains the number of times the station has made the transition from the ring not operational state to the ring operational state.

lpFiNcMacOperTable.name: lpFiNcMacOperTable
lpFiNcMacOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Fddi component related to non-canonical MAC addresses.

lpFiNcMacAddress.name: lpFiNcMacAddress
lpFiNcMacAddress.description: The medium access controller (MAC) address is an address that is recognized by only one station on the attached ring. The value of this attribute is assigned by the system. This attribute is displayed in non- canonical format. The canonical version of this address is indicated in macAddress.

lpFiNcUpstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiNcUpstreamNeighbor
lpFiNcUpstreamNeighbor.description: The ncUpstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the upstream neighbor station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in non-canonical format. The canonical version of this address is indicated in upstreamNeighbor.

lpFiNcDownstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiNcDownstreamNeighbor
lpFiNcDownstreamNeighbor.description: The ncDownstreamNeighbor attribute contains the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in non-canonical format. The canonical version of this address is indicated in downstreamNeighbor

lpFiNcOldUpstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiNcOldUpstreamNeighbor
lpFiNcOldUpstreamNeighbor.description: The ncOldUpstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the upstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in non-canonical format. The canonical version of this address is indicated in oldUpstreamNeighbor.

lpFiNcOldDownstreamNeighbor.name: lpFiNcOldDownstreamNeighbor
lpFiNcOldDownstreamNeighbor.description: The ncOldDownstreamNeighbor attribute contains the previous value of the MAC address associated with the downstream station on the ring. This attribute is displayed in non-canonical format. The canonical version of this address is indicated in oldDownstreamNeighbor.

lpFiPhyLerCutoff.name: lpFiPhyLerCutoff
lpFiPhyLerCutoff.description: The lerCutoff attribute contains the link error rate estimate at which a link connection will be broken. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported.

lpFiPhyLerAlarm.name: lpFiPhyLerAlarm
lpFiPhyLerAlarm.description: The lerAlarm attribute contains the link error rate estimate at which a link connection will generate an alarm. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported

lpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor.name: lpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor
lpFiPhyLinkErrorMonitor.description: The linkErrorMonitor attribute is used to select the state of the link error monitor for the associated Phy component. If enabled, the link error monitor will send the correct test status to the neighboring station. If disabled, the link error monitor will always send a test passed status to the neighboring station.

lpFiPhyOperTable.name: lpFiPhyOperTable
lpFiPhyOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Fddi Phy component.

lpFiPhyNeighborType.name: lpFiPhyNeighborType
lpFiPhyNeighborType.description: This attribute indicates the neighbor type of the neighbor physical layer.

lpFiPhyLctFailCounts.name: lpFiPhyLctFailCounts
lpFiPhyLctFailCounts.description: The lctFailCounts attribute contains the number of consecutive times the Link Confidence Test (LCT) has failed. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiPhyLerEstimate.name: lpFiPhyLerEstimate
lpFiPhyLerEstimate.description: The lerEstimate attribute contains a long term average link error rate. The values will range from 10**-4 to 10**-15. Only the absolute value of the base 10 log is reported

lpFiPhyLemRejectCounts.name: lpFiPhyLemRejectCounts
lpFiPhyLemRejectCounts.description: The lemRejectCounts attribute contains the number of times that a link has been rejected. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiPhyLemCounts.name: lpFiPhyLemCounts
lpFiPhyLemCounts.description: The lemCounts attribute contains the aggregate link error monitor error count. This counter is set to zero only on station initialization. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpFiPhyPcmState.name: lpFiPhyPcmState
lpFiPhyPcmState.description: The pcmState, physical connection manager (PCM), state indicates the current state of the PCM state machine.

lpFiPhyLerFlag.name: lpFiPhyLerFlag
lpFiPhyLerFlag.description: The lerFlag attribute indicates when the link error rate estimate is less than or equal to the link error rate alarm. If true, the value of the link error rate estimate is less than or equal to the link error rate alarm. If false, the value of the link error rate estimate is greater than the link error rate alarm.

lpFiPhySignalState.name: lpFiPhySignalState
lpFiPhySignalState.description: The signalState attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bit being transmitted, or was transmitted, during the PCM signal state.

lpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd.name: lpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd
lpFiPhySignalBitsRcvd.description: The signalBitsRcvd attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bits received. Description of bits: escape(0) phyTypeL(1) phyTypeH(2) accept(3) lctLengthL(4) lctLengthH(5) macAvail(6) lctResult(7) macLoop(8) macOnPhy(9)

lpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt.name: lpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt
lpFiPhySignalBitsTxmt.description: The signalBitsTxmt attribute contains the current physical connection manager (PCM) signal bits transmitted. Description of bits: escape(0) phyTypeL(1) phyTypeH(2) accept(3) lctLengthL(4) lctLengthH(5) macAvail(6) lctResult(7) macLoop(8) macOnPhy(9)

lpFiTestType.name: lpFiTestType
lpFiTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

lpFiTestFrmSize.name: lpFiTestFrmSize
lpFiTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

lpFiTestDuration.name: lpFiTestDuration
lpFiTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

lpFiTestResultsTable.name: lpFiTestResultsTable
lpFiTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

lpFiTestElapsedTime.name: lpFiTestElapsedTime
lpFiTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

lpFiTestTimeRemaining.name: lpFiTestTimeRemaining
lpFiTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

lpFiTestCauseOfTermination.name: lpFiTestCauseOfTermination
lpFiTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

lpFiTestFrmTx.name: lpFiTestFrmTx
lpFiTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpFiTestBitsTx.name: lpFiTestBitsTx
lpFiTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpFiTestFrmRx.name: lpFiTestFrmRx
lpFiTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpFiTestBitsRx.name: lpFiTestBitsRx
lpFiTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpFiTestErroredFrmRx.name: lpFiTestErroredFrmRx
lpFiTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpTrComponentName.description: This variable provides the component's string name for use with the ASCII Console Interface

lpTrStorageType.description: This variable represents the storage type value for the lpTr tables.

lpTrIndex.description: This variable represents the index for the lpTr tables.

lpTrCidDataTable.name: lpTrCidDataTable
lpTrCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

lpTrCustomerIdentifier.name: lpTrCustomerIdentifier
lpTrCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

lpTrIfEntryTable.name: lpTrIfEntryTable
lpTrIfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

lpTrIfAdminStatus.name: lpTrIfAdminStatus
lpTrIfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpTrIfIndex.name: lpTrIfIndex
lpTrIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

lpTrProvTable.name: lpTrProvTable
lpTrProvTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes of the Token Ring port.

lpTrRingSpeed.name: lpTrRingSpeed
lpTrRingSpeed.description: This attribute indicates the ring speed at the next insertion into the ring. Note that all the interfaces on a ring must operate at the same speed.

lpTrMonitorParticipate.name: lpTrMonitorParticipate
lpTrMonitorParticipate.description: This attribute determines whether the interface will participate in the active monitor selection process.

lpTrFunctionalAddress.name: lpTrFunctionalAddress
lpTrFunctionalAddress.description: This attribute contains a bit mask of all token ring functional addresses for which this interface will accept frames. The address is displayed in canonical form.

lpTrNodeAddress.name: lpTrNodeAddress
lpTrNodeAddress.description: This attribute identifies the primary, node specific address recognized by this interface. If an operator does not provision a MAC address, the interface will use a predefined, permanently assigned address. A valid node address must not be any of the following: a broadcast address, a group address, a functional address or a null address. A node address should be entered in the canonical form.

lpTrGroupAddress.name: lpTrGroupAddress
lpTrGroupAddress.description: This attribute identifies the group address for which this interface will accept frames. The address is displayed in canonical form. For a valid group address, the least significant bit of the first octet should be set to 1. Currently, only one group address can be provisioned for one interface.

lpTrProductId.name: lpTrProductId
lpTrProductId.description: This attribute is used to identify the host system attached to this interface. This information is transmitted in response to Request Station Attachment MAC frames.

lpTrApplicationFramerName.name: lpTrApplicationFramerName
lpTrApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Tr component.

lpTrAdminInfoTable.name: lpTrAdminInfoTable
lpTrAdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

lpTrVendor.name: lpTrVendor
lpTrVendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

lpTrCommentText.name: lpTrCommentText
lpTrCommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

lpTrStateTable.name: lpTrStateTable
lpTrStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

lpTrAdminState.name: lpTrAdminState
lpTrAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

lpTrOperationalState.name: lpTrOperationalState
lpTrOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

lpTrUsageState.name: lpTrUsageState
lpTrUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

lpTrOperStatusTable.name: lpTrOperStatusTable
lpTrOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

lpTrSnmpOperStatus.name: lpTrSnmpOperStatus
lpTrSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpTrOperTable.name: lpTrOperTable
lpTrOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the Token Ring component.

lpTrMacAddress.name: lpTrMacAddress
lpTrMacAddress.description: This attribute contains the actual MAC address. The value is assigned by the system if nodeAddress is not provisioned. This address is displayed in canonical form. The non-canonical version of this address is indicated in ncMacAddress.

lpTrRingState.name: lpTrRingState
lpTrRingState.description: This attribute contains the value of the current interface state with respect to entering or leaving the ring.

lpTrRingStatus.name: lpTrRingStatus
lpTrRingStatus.description: This attribute contains the value of the current interface status after the station has entered the ring. The value is a sum of values, one for each currently applicable condition. Before the station attempts an open this attribute has the value of noStatus. noProblems = 0, ringRecovery = 32, singleStation = 64, removeReceived = 256, reserved = 512, autoRemovalError = 1024, lobeWireFault = 2048, transmitBeacon = 4096, softError = 8192, hardError = 16384, signalLoss = 32768, noStatus = 131072 Description of bits: noProblems(0) notused1(1) notused2(2) notused3(3) notused4(4) ringRecovery(5) singleStation(6) notused7(7) removeReceived(8) reserved(9) autoRemovalError(10) lobeWireFault(11) transmitBeacon(12) softError(13) hardError(14) signalLoss(15) notused16(16) noStatus(17)

lpTrRingOpenStatus.name: lpTrRingOpenStatus
lpTrRingOpenStatus.description: This attribute indicates what happened the last time the station attempted to enter into the ring.

lpTrUpStream.name: lpTrUpStream
lpTrUpStream.description: This attribute is the MAC address of the station's up-stream neighbor. This address is displayed in canonical form. The non- canonical version of this address is indicated in ncUpStream.

lpTrChipSet.name: lpTrChipSet
lpTrChipSet.description: This attribute identifies the hardware chip set in use by an interface.

lpTrLastTimeBeaconSent.name: lpTrLastTimeBeaconSent
lpTrLastTimeBeaconSent.description: This attribute indicates the time at which a Beacon frame was last transmitted on this interface.

lpTrStatsTable.name: lpTrStatsTable
lpTrStatsTable.description: This group contains statistical information for the Token Ring port.

lpTrLineErrors.name: lpTrLineErrors
lpTrLineErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of frames or tokens copied or repeated by a station where there is a non-data bit or a FCS error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrBurstErrors.name: lpTrBurstErrors
lpTrBurstErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times the station detects the absence of transitions for five consecutive half-bit times. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrAcErrors.name: lpTrAcErrors
lpTrAcErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times that a station can not set the AC bits properly. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrAbortTransErrors.name: lpTrAbortTransErrors
lpTrAbortTransErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of aborted frames. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrInternalErrors.name: lpTrInternalErrors
lpTrInternalErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of internal errors. When the value of the counter soars up quickly, it indicates a potential hardware problem. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrLostFrameErrors.name: lpTrLostFrameErrors
lpTrLostFrameErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station is transmitting and its TRR timer expires. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrReceiveCongestions.name: lpTrReceiveCongestions
lpTrReceiveCongestions.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station is supposed to receive a frame but cannot due to lack of buffer space. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrFrameCopiedErrors.name: lpTrFrameCopiedErrors
lpTrFrameCopiedErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station receives a frame addressed to its specific address and detects that the A bit is set. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrTokenErrors.name: lpTrTokenErrors
lpTrTokenErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times a station acting as the active monitor recognizes an error condition that needs a token transmission. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrSoftErrors.name: lpTrSoftErrors
lpTrSoftErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of soft errors or the number of Report Error Mac frames the station has transmitted. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrHardErrors.name: lpTrHardErrors
lpTrHardErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of times this interface has detected an immediately recoverable fatal error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrSignalLoss.name: lpTrSignalLoss
lpTrSignalLoss.description: This attribute contains the number of times signal condition has been lost. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrTransmitBeacons.name: lpTrTransmitBeacons
lpTrTransmitBeacons.description: This attribute contains the number of beacon frames transmitted. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrRingRecoverys.name: lpTrRingRecoverys
lpTrRingRecoverys.description: This attribute contains the number of times the ring has been purged. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrLobeWires.name: lpTrLobeWires
lpTrLobeWires.description: This attribute contains the number of times the interface has detected a short circuit in the lobe data path. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrRemoveRings.name: lpTrRemoveRings
lpTrRemoveRings.description: This attribute contains the number of Remove Ring Station Mac frames received. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrSingleStation.name: lpTrSingleStation
lpTrSingleStation.description: This attribute contains the number of times the station has determined it is the only one on the ring. This is not necessarily an error. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrFreqErrors.name: lpTrFreqErrors
lpTrFreqErrors.description: This attribute contains the number of signal frequency errors detected. This counter wraps around when the maximum value is reached.

lpTrNcMacOperTable.description: This group contains the operational attributes of the TokenRing port component related to non-canonical MAC addresses.

lpTrNcMacAddress.description: This attribute contains the actual MAC address. The value is assigned by the system if nodeAddress is not provisioned. This address is displayed in non-canonical form. The canonical version of this address is indicated in macAddress.

lpTrNcUpStream.name: lpTrNcUpStream
lpTrNcUpStream.description: This attribute is the MAC address of the station's up-stream neighbor. This address is displayed in non-canonical form. The canonical version of this address is indicated in upStream.

lpTrTestType.name: lpTrTestType
lpTrTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

lpTrTestFrmSize.name: lpTrTestFrmSize
lpTrTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

lpTrTestDuration.name: lpTrTestDuration
lpTrTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

lpTrTestResultsTable.name: lpTrTestResultsTable
lpTrTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

lpTrTestElapsedTime.name: lpTrTestElapsedTime
lpTrTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

lpTrTestTimeRemaining.name: lpTrTestTimeRemaining
lpTrTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

lpTrTestCauseOfTermination.name: lpTrTestCauseOfTermination
lpTrTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

lpTrTestFrmTx.name: lpTrTestFrmTx
lpTrTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpTrTestBitsTx.name: lpTrTestBitsTx
lpTrTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpTrTestFrmRx.name: lpTrTestFrmRx
lpTrTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpTrTestBitsRx.name: lpTrTestBitsRx
lpTrTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpTrTestErroredFrmRx.name: lpTrTestErroredFrmRx
lpTrTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrIfIndex.name: lpIlsFwdrIfIndex
lpIlsFwdrIfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

lpIlsFwdrStateTable.name: lpIlsFwdrStateTable
lpIlsFwdrStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

lpIlsFwdrAdminState.name: lpIlsFwdrAdminState
lpIlsFwdrAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

lpIlsFwdrOperationalState.name: lpIlsFwdrOperationalState
lpIlsFwdrOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

lpIlsFwdrUsageState.name: lpIlsFwdrUsageState
lpIlsFwdrUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

lpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable.name: lpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable
lpIlsFwdrOperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

lpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus.name: lpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus
lpIlsFwdrSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpIlsFwdrStatsTable.name: lpIlsFwdrStatsTable
lpIlsFwdrStatsTable.description: This group contains the operational frame statistics related attributes of the IlsForwarder component.

lpIlsFwdrFramesReceived.name: lpIlsFwdrFramesReceived
lpIlsFwdrFramesReceived.description: This attribute counts the total number of frames that have been received by this card. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrProcessedCount.name: lpIlsFwdrProcessedCount
lpIlsFwdrProcessedCount.description: This attribute counts the number of frames successfully processed by this card. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrErrorCount.name: lpIlsFwdrErrorCount
lpIlsFwdrErrorCount.description: This attribute counts the number of internal errors detected in transferring frames from an ATM card to this card. A continuous increment of this count indicates that the hardware may probably be defective. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded.name: lpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded
lpIlsFwdrFramesDiscarded.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which are discarded due to local buffer congestion. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrTestType.name: lpIlsFwdrTestType
lpIlsFwdrTestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

lpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize.name: lpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize
lpIlsFwdrTestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

lpIlsFwdrTestDuration.name: lpIlsFwdrTestDuration
lpIlsFwdrTestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

lpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable.name: lpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable
lpIlsFwdrTestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

lpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime.name: lpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime
lpIlsFwdrTestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

lpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining.name: lpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining
lpIlsFwdrTestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

lpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination.name: lpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination
lpIlsFwdrTestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

lpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx.name: lpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx
lpIlsFwdrTestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx.name: lpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx
lpIlsFwdrTestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx.name: lpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx
lpIlsFwdrTestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx.name: lpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx
lpIlsFwdrTestBitsRx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx.name: lpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx
lpIlsFwdrTestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpEth100CustomerIdentifier.name: lpEth100CustomerIdentifier
lpEth100CustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

lpEth100IfEntryTable.description: This group contains the provisionable attributes for the ifEntry.

lpEth100IfAdminStatus.name: lpEth100IfAdminStatus
lpEth100IfAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational. The down state indicates the interface is not operational. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpEth100IfIndex.name: lpEth100IfIndex
lpEth100IfIndex.description: This is the index for the IfEntry. Its value is automatically initialized during the provisioning process.

lpEth100ProvTable.name: lpEth100ProvTable

lpEth100DuplexMode.name: lpEth100DuplexMode
lpEth100DuplexMode.description: This attribute specifies the duplex mode of the port. This attribute is ignored if auto negotiation is successful.

lpEth100LineSpeed.name: lpEth100LineSpeed
lpEth100LineSpeed.description: This attribute sets the operating speed for the Ethernet 100BaseT port. This attribute is ignored if auto negotiation is successful.

lpEth100AutoNegotiation.name: lpEth100AutoNegotiation
lpEth100AutoNegotiation.description: This attribute is used to select whether or not the port does auto negotiation. The provisionable values of duplexMode and lineSpeed are ignored if auto negotiation is successful. Refer to the operational attribute autoNegStatus for auto negotiation results.

lpEth100ApplicationFramerName.name: lpEth100ApplicationFramerName
lpEth100ApplicationFramerName.description: This attribute contains the component name of a Framer which is associated with the Eth100BaseT component. This defines which Lan Application will be using this Eth100BaseT interface.

lpEth100AdminInfoTable.name: lpEth100AdminInfoTable
lpEth100AdminInfoTable.description: This group contains the attributes pertaining to the vendor of the equipment.

lpEth100Vendor.name: lpEth100Vendor
lpEth100Vendor.description: This is the name of the vendor supplying the facility.

lpEth100CommentText.name: lpEth100CommentText
lpEth100CommentText.description: Any miscellaneous text about the facility.

lpEth100StateTable.name: lpEth100StateTable
lpEth100StateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

lpEth100AdminState.name: lpEth100AdminState
lpEth100AdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

lpEth100OperationalState.name: lpEth100OperationalState
lpEth100OperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

lpEth100UsageState.name: lpEth100UsageState
lpEth100UsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

lpEth100OperStatusTable.name: lpEth100OperStatusTable
lpEth100OperStatusTable.description: This group includes the Operational Status attribute. This attribute defines the current operational state of this component.

lpEth100SnmpOperStatus.name: lpEth100SnmpOperStatus
lpEth100SnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

lpEth100OperTable.name: lpEth100OperTable
lpEth100OperTable.description: This group contains the Port operational attributes of the Eth100BaseT component.

lpEth100MacAddress.name: lpEth100MacAddress
lpEth100MacAddress.description: This attribute indicates the medium access controller (MAC) address. The MAC address is displayed in canonical format.

lpEth100AutoNegStatus.name: lpEth100AutoNegStatus
lpEth100AutoNegStatus.description: This attribute displays the status of the auto negotiation at the Phy level.

lpEth100ActualLineSpeed.name: lpEth100ActualLineSpeed
lpEth100ActualLineSpeed.description: This attribute indicates the line speed of the Eth100BaseT port.

lpEth100ActualDuplexMode.name: lpEth100ActualDuplexMode
lpEth100ActualDuplexMode.description: This attribute indicates whether the hardware is in half duplex or full duplex mode.

lpEth100Eth100StatsTable.name: lpEth100Eth100StatsTable
lpEth100Eth100StatsTable.description: This group contains the statistical attributes for the Eth100BaseT component.

lpEth100FramesTransmittedOk.name: lpEth100FramesTransmittedOk
lpEth100FramesTransmittedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were transmitted without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100FramesReceivedOk.name: lpEth100FramesReceivedOk
lpEth100FramesReceivedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were received without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk.name: lpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk
lpEth100OctetsTransmittedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of octets which were transmitted without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100OctetsReceivedOk.name: lpEth100OctetsReceivedOk
lpEth100OctetsReceivedOk.description: This attribute counts the number of octets which were received without errors. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100UndersizeFrames.name: lpEth100UndersizeFrames
lpEth100UndersizeFrames.description: This attribute counts the number of frames that were received but were less than the minimum size (64 bytes). This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr.name: lpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr
lpEth100ReceivedOctetsIntoRouterBr.description: This attribute counts the number of octets that were not hardware switched but were passed the Router or Bridge software. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr.name: lpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr
lpEth100ReceivedFramesIntoRouterBr.description: This attribute counts the number of frames which were not hardware switched but were passed to the Router or Bridge software. This counter wraps to zero after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100StatsTable.name: lpEth100StatsTable
lpEth100StatsTable.description: This group contains statistical attributes for the Ethernet component.

lpEth100AlignmentErrors.name: lpEth100AlignmentErrors
lpEth100AlignmentErrors.description: The alignmentErrors counter indicates the number of frames received which were not an integral number of octets in length. Frames will be checked for alignmentErrors before they are checked for Frame Check Sequence (FCS) errors. If there is an alignment error, the error will only be counted here and not in fcsErrors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100FcsErrors.name: lpEth100FcsErrors
lpEth100FcsErrors.description: The fcsErrors, Frame Check Sequence (FCS) error, counter indicates the number of frames received which were an integral number of octets in length and did not pass the FCS check. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100SingleCollisionFrames.name: lpEth100SingleCollisionFrames
lpEth100SingleCollisionFrames.description: The singleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced exactly one collision. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames.name: lpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames
lpEth100MultipleCollisionFrames.description: The multipleCollisionFrames counter indicates the number of frames successfully transmitted which experienced more than one collision. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100SqeTestErrors.name: lpEth100SqeTestErrors
lpEth100SqeTestErrors.description: The sqeTestErrors, Signal Quality Error (SQE) Test errors, counter indicates the number of times the 'SQE Test Error' message has been generated for the station. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100DeferredTransmissions.name: lpEth100DeferredTransmissions
lpEth100DeferredTransmissions.description: The deferredTransmissions counter indicates the number of frames which experienced a transmission delay because the medium was busy. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100LateCollisions.name: lpEth100LateCollisions
lpEth100LateCollisions.description: The lateCollisions counter indicates the number of times a collision was detected later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100ExcessiveCollisions.name: lpEth100ExcessiveCollisions
lpEth100ExcessiveCollisions.description: The excessiveCollisions counter indicates the number of frames which failed to get transmitted due to excessive collisions. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100MacTransmitErrors.name: lpEth100MacTransmitErrors
lpEth100MacTransmitErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) transmit error counter indicates the number of times that a transmission failed due to internal MAC transmit errors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100CarrierSenseErrors.name: lpEth100CarrierSenseErrors
lpEth100CarrierSenseErrors.description: The carrier sense error counter indicates the number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100FrameTooLongs.name: lpEth100FrameTooLongs
lpEth100FrameTooLongs.description: The frame too long counter indicates the number of frames received which exceeded the maximum frame size. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100MacReceiveErrors.name: lpEth100MacReceiveErrors
lpEth100MacReceiveErrors.description: The Medium Access Controller (MAC) receive error counter indicates the number of times a receive failed due to internal MAC receive errors. This counter will wrap around after it reaches its maximum value.

lpEth100TestType.name: lpEth100TestType
lpEth100TestType.description: This attribute is the type of test to be run. The available test types include the following: card test sets up an internal loop on the board and runs a bit error rate test; manual test assumes the line is looped back externally and a bit error rate test is performed; localLoop test loops back the local modem and performs a bit error rate test; remoteLoop test loops back the remote modem (or CSU) and performs a bit error rate test; externalLoop test loops back the line to the far end; payloadLoop test only loops back the payload data received from the incoming line; Note that localLoop, remoteLoop and payloadLoop are not supported by all function processors.

lpEth100TestFrmSize.name: lpEth100TestFrmSize
lpEth100TestFrmSize.description: This attribute defines the size of the test data frames in number of bytes.

lpEth100TestDuration.name: lpEth100TestDuration
lpEth100TestDuration.description: This attribute is the duration (in minutes) that test data will be transmitted. In the case of an externalLoop, this is the time that the loop is in effect. Note that dataStartDelay does not apply to the externalLoop.

lpEth100TestResultsTable.name: lpEth100TestResultsTable
lpEth100TestResultsTable.description: This group contains all the statistics related attributes of the Test component.

lpEth100TestElapsedTime.name: lpEth100TestElapsedTime
lpEth100TestElapsedTime.description: This attribute is the number of minutes elapsed since the test started for an externalLoop test. For a data test, this is the time since test data was first transmitted.

lpEth100TestTimeRemaining.name: lpEth100TestTimeRemaining
lpEth100TestTimeRemaining.description: This attribute is the number of minutes remaining before the test is to be stopped according to the duration attribute.

lpEth100TestCauseOfTermination.name: lpEth100TestCauseOfTermination
lpEth100TestCauseOfTermination.description: This attribute records the reason the test is terminated.

lpEth100TestFrmTx.name: lpEth100TestFrmTx
lpEth100TestFrmTx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpEth100TestBitsTx.name: lpEth100TestBitsTx
lpEth100TestBitsTx.description: This attribute is the total number of bits sent during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value.

lpEth100TestFrmRx.name: lpEth100TestFrmRx
lpEth100TestFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

lpEth100TestBitsRx.name: lpEth100TestBitsRx

lpEth100TestErroredFrmRx.description: This attribute is the total number of errored frames received during the test period. This counter is not expected to reach its maximum value. The counter will wrap around to 0 if it does reach its maximum value.

laCidDataTable.description: This group contains the attribute for a component's Customer Identifier (CID). Refer to the attribute description for a detailed explanation of CIDs.

laCustomerIdentifier.name: laCustomerIdentifier
laCustomerIdentifier.description: This attribute holds the Customer Identifier (CID). Every component has a CID. If a component has a cid attribute, the component's CID is the provisioned value of that attribute; otherwise the component inherits the CID of its parent. The top- level component has a CID of 0. Every operator session also has a CID, which is the CID provisioned for the operator's user ID. An operator will see only the stream data for components having a matching CID. Also, the operator will be allowed to issue commands for only those components which have a matching CID. An operator CID of 0 is used to identify the Network Manager (referred to as 'NetMan' in DPN). This CID matches the CID of any component. Values 1 to 8191 inclusive (equivalent to 'basic CIDs' in DPN) may be assigned to specific customers.

laStateTable.name: laStateTable
laStateTable.description: This group contains the three OSI State attributes. The descriptions generically indicate what each state attribute implies about the component. Note that not all the values and state combinations described here are supported by every component which uses this group. For component-specific information and the valid state combinations, refer to NTP 241-7001-150, Passport Operations and Maintenance Guide.

laAdminState.name: laAdminState
laAdminState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Administrative State of the component. The value locked indicates that the component is administratively prohibited from providing services for its users. A Lock or Lock - force command has been previously issued for this component. When the value is locked, the value of usageState must be idle. The value shuttingDown indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide service to its existing users only. A Lock command was issued against the component and it is in the process of shutting down. The value unlocked indicates that the component is administratively permitted to provide services for its users. To enter this state, issue an Unlock command to this component.

laOperationalState.name: laOperationalState
laOperationalState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Operational State of the component. The value enabled indicates that the component is available for operation. Note that if adminState is locked, it would still not be providing service. The value disabled indicates that the component is not available for operation. For example, something is wrong with the component itself, or with another component on which this one depends. If the value is disabled, the usageState must be idle.

laUsageState.name: laUsageState
laUsageState.description: This attribute indicates the OSI Usage State of the component. The value idle indicates that the component is not currently in use. The value active indicates that the component is in use and has spare capacity to provide for additional users. The value busy indicates that the component is in use and has no spare operating capacity for additional users at this time.

laSnmpOperStatus.name: laSnmpOperStatus
laSnmpOperStatus.description: The current state of the interface. The up state indicates the interface is operational and capable of forwarding packets. The down state indicates the interface is not operational, thus unable to forward packets. testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.
